          <ownedFunctionalChains xsi:type="org.polarsys.capella.core.data.fa:FunctionalChain"
              id="5c91f6f2-74fc-4b77-9b67-41764d4222a1" name="Bleed celll" description="&lt;ol>&#xA;&#x9;&lt;li style=&quot;margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;tab-stops: list .5in;&quot;>&lt;b>Passive Balancing&lt;/b>:&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&#xA;&#x9;&lt;ul style=&quot;list-style-type: disc;&quot;>&#xA;&#x9;&#x9;&lt;li style=&quot;margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;tab-stops: list 1.0in;&quot;>&lt;b>Resistive Bleeding&lt;/b>: Passive balancing typically involves discharging the energy from higher-charged cells through a resistive path to dissipate the excess energy as heat.&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/li>&#xA;&#x9;&#x9;&lt;li style=&quot;margin-top: 16px; margin-bottom: 16px;&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-style: normal;&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: normal;&quot;>&lt;span style=&quot;tab-stops: list 1.0in;&quot;>&lt;b>Equalization&lt;/b>: The goal is to equalize the SOC of all cells by letting the more charged cells lose energy until they match the level of the least charged cell.&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/li>&#xA;&#x9;&lt;/ul>&#xA;&#x9;&lt;/li>&#xA;&lt;/ol>&#xA;">
            <ownedFunctionalChainInvolvements xsi:type="org.polarsys.capella.core.data.fa:FunctionalChainInvolvementLink"
